Qh5+ Kxf8 20. Rb6 $16) (9... Nd6 $6 10. Bf4 e6 11. Nc3 $16 {[%cal Gc3d5,Gd1f3]}
) 10. Bg5 e6 (10... Nc6 11. Bxf6 gxf6 12. Nxc6 dxc6 13. Qf3 {[%cal Gf3c6,Gf3f6]
} Qd7 (13... Bg7 14. Qxc6+ Kf8 15. Nc3 Qc8 16. Qf3 $16) 14. Qxf6 Rg8 15. Nc3
$16) (10... Qb6 $6 11. Nc3 Nc6 12. Bxf6 gxf6 13. Nf5 $16 {[%cal Gc3d5]}) 11.
Nc3 Be7 (11... Nc6 12. Nxc6 dxc6 13. Qf3 {[%cal Ga1d1,Gf3c6,Gc3e4]} Be7 14.
Qxc6+ {transforms to a line, covered later.}) 12. Qf3 Nc6 (12... Ra7 $6 13. Nf5
$3 exf5 14. Bxf6 gxf6 15. Nd5 Nc6 16. Rxe7+ Nxe7 17. Qe3 {[%cal Ge3a7,Gd5f6,
Ge3h6]} h5 (17... Rb7 $4 18. Nxf6+ Kf8 19. Qh6#) 18. Nxf6+ Kf8 19. Qxa7 $16) (
12... d5 13. Nf5 $1 exf5 14. Bxf6 gxf6 15. Nxd5 Ra7 16. Rad1 O-O 17. Rxe7 Rxe7
18. Nxf6+ Kg7 19. Rxd8 Rxd8 20. Qxf5 $18) 13. Nxc6 dxc6 14. Qxc6+ Kf8 15. Rad1
Qc8 16. Qf3 h6 17. Bf4 $14) (7... Nxe4 {probably a slightly better choice to
keep the bishops on the board as the c6 square remains protected.} 8. Re1 {
now if Black retreats with the bishop, we reach a similar position with the
