Bxe4 Ne6 12. Nc3 Nc5 13. Bg2 $18) 10. Nc3 {around this time Black probably
should realize that he should bail out of the danger and give back the
material, but how?} Nd7 {the best try} (10... g6 11. Nxd5 Bxd5 12. Bxe4 Bxe4
13. Rxe4 Bg7 14. Bg5 O-O 15. Bxe7 Qd5 16. Bxf8 Qxe4 17. Bxg7 Kxg7 18. Rc1 Nd7
19. Rxc4 Nb6 20. Rc1 $16) (10... Nf6 11. Bg5 {is the same sad story for Black
that was already covered in a different line}) (10... Nxc3 11. bxc3 $18 {
[%cal Ga1b1,Gc1a3,Gg2h3]}) (10... Qd7 11. Nxd5 Bxd5 12. Bxe4 Bxe4 13. Rxe4 Nc6
14. Qf3 $1 Rc8 15. Be3 $16) (10... Nc5 11. Qh5 {[%cal Gc3d5]} Nd3 12. Nxd5 $1
Nxe1 13. Ne6 Qd6 14. Ndc7+ Kd7 15. Nc5+ Kxc7 16. Nxb7 $18 {[%cal Gc1f4]}) 11.
Nxe4 dxe4 12. Qa4 $1 {[%cal Ga4e8] a very annoying pin!} e6 13. Bxe4 Bxe4 (
13... Qb6 14. Bxb7 Qxb7 15. Qxc4 {[%cal Gd4e6,Ge1e6]} Qb4 {[%cal Rb4c4,Rb4e1]
it would seem that Black is out of the danger, if not for the fascinating
White's next move.} (15... Be7 16. Nxe6 fxe6 17. Rxe6 $16) 16. Rxe6+ $3 fxe6
17. Qxe6+ Be7 (17... Qe7 18. Qc6 Rb8 19. Bf4 Rb6 20. Qc8+ Qd8 21. Qc4 $16 {
[%cal Ga1e1,Gd4c6] things can't end well for Black.}) 18. Nf5 Rf8 (18... g6 19.
Ng7+ Kd8 20. Bf4 $18) 19. Bd2 Qc5 20. Nxg7+ Kd8 21. Qe2 {[%cal Gg7e6]} Qe5 22.
