Be3 O-O 16. Nc6 Qe8 17. Rxc4 $14 {White is definitely better but at least
Black still lives.}) (7... d6 8. Re1 {[%cal Ge4e5,Gc1g5]} e5 (8... Qc8 9. Bg5
Nbd7 10. Nc3 e6 11. a4 b4 12. Nd5 $1 {is a standard idea and it will be
analyzed in later chapters.}) 9. a4 $1 Nc6 (9... exd4 $2 10. e5 dxe5 11. Rxe5+
Be7 12. Bxb7 $16) 10. Nf5 g6 11. axb5 axb5 12. Rxa8 Bxa8 13. Ne3 $16) (7... Nc6
$2 8. e5) 8. Re1 {[%cal Ge4e5]} d5 (8... d6 9. Bg5 {improving the e4-e5 threat.
} ({the immediate} 9. e5 Bxg2 10. exf6 Bb7 11. Bg5 Qd7 12. Nc3 {looks good for
White as well.}) 9... Qc7 (9... Nbd7 $4 10. e5 Bxg2 11. exf6 gxf6 12. Kxg2 fxg5
13. Rxe6+ $1 fxe6 14. Qh5+ Ke7 15. Nc6+ $18) (9... Qb6 10. Bxf6 gxf6 11. Nc3
