main line of this database as Black has not played d7-d6 yet and probably
shouldn't!} Nc6 7. Be3 Qb6) 5... d6 {is the classical Dragon - the top players
in the World avoid playing it with Black.}) (4... Bg7 {is also possible and in
most occasions will lead to the same positions.} 5. c4 Nc6 6. Be3 Nf6 {[%cal
Rf6g4]} (6... Qb6 {the pin supposedly looks dangerous but it is not} 7. Nb3 Qc7
8. Qd2 Nf6 9. f3 O-O 10. Nc3 $14 {[%cal Ga1c1,Gf1e2,Ge1g1]}) (6... Nh6 {
[%cal Rf7f5] This is a rather interesting possibility for Black - he is aiming
for a f7-f5 push in the very near future. The lines are quite forced and as
