along the way. Even if Black got this far, White can press a little more if he
keeps rooks on the board.}) 19... b5 $1 $146 {a very logical novelty} (19... f4
20. Bf2 Ne5 21. Nd5 Bxd5 22. cxd5 Rac8 23. Rxc8 Rxc8 24. Rc1 Rxc1 25. Kxc1 $14
{Black has to defend a really unpleasant endgame.} Kf7 26. Be1 Bf6 27. h4 h6
28. Kc2 e6 29. Bd2 Bxh4 30. Bxf4 Bg5 31. Bg3 Ng6 32. dxe6+ Kxe6 33. Bd3 Ne7 34.
f4 Bf6 35. Be4 Nc6 36. Bf5+ Ke7 37. Bc8 b6 38. Be1 a5 39. Bd2 Nb4+ 40. Kb1 Nd5
41. a4 Bd4 42. Bb7 Bc3 43. Bc1 Nf6 44. Kc2 Ba1 45. Bf3 Nd7 46. Kd3 Nc5+ 47. Kc4
Bg7 48. Bd5 Kd7 49. Be3 Kc7 50. g5 hxg5 51. fxg5 Kd7 52. Kb5 Kc7 53. g6 Nd7 54.
Be6 Nc5 55. Bf7 Nd7 56. Kc4 Ne5+ 57. Kd5 Ng4 58. Bd4 Nf6+ 59. Ke6 Nh5 60. Bxg7
Nxg7+ 61. Kf6 Nh5+ 62. Kg5 Ng7 63. Bd5 Kb8 64. Kf6 Nh5+ 65. Kf7 {1-0 (65)
Pikula,D (2471)-Baglan,E (2314) Veliko Gradiste 2018}) (19... Rad8 {[%cal
Rd6d5,Rd7f6]} 20. g5 $6 (20. Nd5 $146 Bxd5 21. cxd5 Nf6 22. Bd3 Nxd5 23. Bxf5
Nxe3 24. Kxe3 Bh6+ 25. f4 $14 {[%cal Gc1c7]}) 20... f4 21. Bf2 Ne5 22. Nd5 Rd7
23. h4 h6 (23... b5 $13) 24. gxh6 Bxh6 25. Rhg1+ Kh7 26. Bd4 b5 27. Bxe5 dxe5
28. Bd3+ Bf5 29. Bxf5+ Rxf5 30. Ke2 bxc4 31. bxc4 $16 {1-0 (48) Wojtaszek,R 
(2749)-Brendel,O (2324) Tallinn 2016}) (19... Rac8 $146 20. f4 Nf6 21. Rhg1 {
[%cal Ge2f3]} Ne4+ 22. Nxe4 fxe4 23. f5 Bd7 24. Bg5 $14 {[%cal Gd2e3]}) 20. Nd5
Bxd5 21. cxd5 f4 22. Bf2 Nf6 23. Bd3 Nxd5 24. Be4 (24. Bf5 $5 {[%cal Gf5e6,
Gc1c7]} Rxf5 25. gxf5 Kf7 $13) 24... e6 25. Bxd5 exd5 26. Rhe1 Be5 27. Kd3 a5 (
27... Rac8 28. Bd4 b4 29. h4 h6 30. Rxc8 Rxc8 31. Bxe5 dxe5 32. Rxe5 Rc3+ 33.
Kd4 Rxf3 34. Rxd5 $14 {[%cal Gd5a5]}) 28. Rc7 a4 29. b4 Rac8 30. Rec1 Rxc7 31.
Rxc7 Rf7 32. Rc8+ Rf8 33. Rc6 {[%cal Gh3h5,Gg4g5] and White is pressing in the
endgame.} *

