13. fxe5 dxe5 14. Nf5 Bc5+ 15. Kh1 O-O 16. Qd2 $16 {[%cal Gd2g5,Gf5g7,Gb2b4,
Gc2c4] White's advantage is obvious}) 10. Bg5 $1 $146 {[%cal Gc3d5] Black is
in trouble!} ({an immediate} 10. Nd5 $5 {is possible but it is less clear.}
exd5 11. exd5+ Ne5 12. c4 $1 Be7 13. Nf5 O-O 14. Nxe7+ Qxe7 15. f4 Nfd7 16. b3
$14) (10. Ncb5 Qc8 $4 (10... Qb8) 11. Bf4 Ne5 12. Nf5 $1 exf5 13. Nxd6+ Bxd6
14. Qxd6 Qe6 15. Qxe5 fxe4 16. Qxe6+ fxe6 17. Be5 Kf7 18. Bxf6 gxf6 19. Bxe4
Bxe4 20. Rxe4 $16 {1/2-1/2 (61) Starostits,I (2474)-Kulaots,K (2570) Liepaja
2005}) 10... Rd8 {apparently the only move which holds Black's position
together - it can be difficult to find! Now the immediate sacrifice is not so
clear.} (10... h6 11. Ncb5 $1 Qc8 (11... Qb8 12. Bxf6 Nxf6 13. e5 dxe5 14. Nc6
$18) 12. Bf4 Ne5 13. Nf5 $1 {the motifs always remain the same.} exf5 14. Nxd6+
Bxd6 15. Qxd6 Qe6 16. Qxe6+ fxe6 17. Bxe5 $16) (10... Be7 $2 11. Ncb5 $1 {
a very important motif to know otherwise Black is just fine! The queen has no
good squares to retreat.} Qb8 (11... Qc8 12. Nf5 $1 exf5 13. exf5 $18 {[%cal
Gb5d6,Ge1e8]}) 12. Bxf6 Nxf6 (12... Bxf6 13. e5 $1 Bxe5 14. Bxb7 Qxb7 15. Rxe5
$18 {[%cal Gb5d6]}) (12... gxf6 13. Qh5 $18 {[%cal Gd4e6,Gg2h3]}) 13. e5 dxe5
14. Nc6 $1 {the point of the combination!} Bxc6 15. Bxc6+ Kf8 16. Bxa8 Qxa8 17.
