Qxf6 14. Nd5 Qf5 15. Nf4 $14 {[%csl Rc5,Gg2]}) 12. b4 Bd6 (12... Be7 13. Ng5
Qd7 14. Bb2 $14 {and at a convenient moment White will take on e6, creating a
weak pawn and enjoying two bishop advantage.}) (12... Bb6 {almost always is
met by} 13. Na4 Bc7 14. Bb2 {[%cal Gd1d3,Gf1e1,Ga1d1]}) 13. Re1 {the rest of
the moves are not forced and merely illustrate what could happen in the game.
At White's disposal are several ideas - play Nb5 with an intention to jump to
an outpost on d4. The dark squared bishop typically goes to b2 but Bg5 at the
right moment might increase the pressure for the d5 pawn. In that case, be
ready that it can be met with Be7 and h6. The white queen typically goes to d3
and it can be rerouted to b3 in case Black chases it away with Qd7 and Bf5.
Rad1 seems like a normal move for every occasion.} Qd7 {[%cal Re6h3] targeting
the h3 pawn but at the moment it's not really a threat as Black's own pawn on
d5 is hanging. It makes sense for White to build up such a strategy which
avoids wasting time to play Kh2.} 14. Bb2 $1 Rfe8 {this allows an interesting
idea which not always might be at White's disposal.} (14... Rad8 15. Nb5 $1 {
[%cal Gb2f6] again, not wasting time to defend the h3 pawn!} Be7 (15... Ne4 16.
Nd2 $1 Nxd2 17. Qxd2 Bxh3 $2 18. Bxg7 $1 Kxg7 19. Bxh3 Qxh3 20. Qg5+ Kh8 21.
Qf6+ Kg8 22. Nxd6 $18) 16. Nfd4 $1 Nxd4 (16... Bxh3 $6 17. Nxc6 bxc6 18. Bxh3
Qxh3 19. Rxe7 cxb5 20. Bxf6 gxf6 21. Qf3 $16) 17. Nxd4 {[%cal Gd4e6,Gd1e2]}) (
14... Bxh3 $6 15. Nxd5 Nxd5 16. Qxd5 Bxg2 17. Kxg2 $16) 15. Nb5 Be7 16. c4 $5 {
certainly not mandatory but very interesting, given the particular position!}
a6 (16... dxc4 $2 17. Qxd7 Nxd7 18. Nc7 $16) (16... Bxh3 $4 {as you can see
from this and other lines, if White is prepared, the pawn on h3 often is
indirectly defended and can't be really taken.} 17. Bxh3 Qxh3 18. cxd5 Rad8 19.
Bxf6 gxf6 20. dxc6 $1 Rxd1 21. Raxd1 bxc6 22. Nc7 $18) 17. cxd5 Nxd5 (17...
Bxd5 18. Nc3 Be6 19. Ng5 $14) 18. Nbd4 Nxd4 (18... Bxh3 $4 19. Nxc6 bxc6 20.
Ne5 Qc8 21. Bxh3 Qxh3 22. Nxc6 Bf6 23. Qxd5 Bxb2 24. Re7 $1 $18 Rf8 25. Rxf7 $1
{[%cal Gc6e7]}) 19. Ne5 $1 Qb5 20. Qxd4 Bf6 21. Rac1 Rac8 22. Qd3 {and White
