{Black has just declined to take on d4 and played 4...Bb7 instead, targeting
the pawn on e4. What will you do?} 5. d5 $1 {[%csl Rb7] the general rule is
that if Black doesn't take on d4 in the Sicilian, in most case you go forward
and grab space.} Nf6 {not only is Black threatening to take on e4, the next
move is going to be 6...e6.} 6. Nfd2 $1 {Dealing with those problems and as it
happens, it's much stronger than the logical Qe2.} e6 7. Bg2 $1 d6 (7... exd5
$6 8. e5 $1 Ne4 9. Nxe4 dxe4 10. Nc3 $16) 8. O-O $1 exd5 9. exd5 {Black can't
really take on d5 because of the exposed king.} Be7 10. c4 O-O 11. Nc3 $14 {
White has secured an obvious advantage.} *

