{Black has just played 12...Nd7 and is inviting White to trade the
dark-squared bishops. What should you do?} 13. Be3 $1 {It's in White's best
interest to keep the dark-squared bishops on the board. While Black will seek
his counterplay, he will create additional weaknesses in the process.} (13.
Rfd1 $6 Bxd4+ 14. Qxd4 Qb6 $1 {if the queens go off the board as well, White's
chances for success are very limited.} 15. Qxb6 Nxb6 $11) 13... a5 14. b3 $1 {
