{Black is proposing a pawn sacrifice after the aggressive 7...Bg4. Can you
take the pawn on e7? What would you play here?} 7. h3 $1 {a very important
move before the next one which keeps all the positional pluses for White.} (7.
dxe7 $6 Qxe7+ 8. Kf1 O-O-O {is very unclear although probably good for White.
Black has the initiative, at least in the short term, but a pawn is a pawn.})
7... Bh5 {Now what?} (7... Bxf3 8. Bxf3 Qxd6 9. Nc3 e6 10. Nxd5 exd5 11. O-O
Be7 12. d3 $14 {[%csl Gf3][%cal Gc2c3,Gc1f4] The light-squared white bishop
will cause Black some headaches in the long run.}) 8. d4 $1 {Despite the fact
that the bishop is pinning the knight, this move is very much possible!} cxd4 (
8... Nxd4 $2 9. g4 {[%csl Rd5] doesn't really work for Black.}) 9. g4 $1 Bg6
10. Nxd4 Qxd6 11. O-O e6 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. c4 Nb4 14. Nc3 {[%csl Rc6] with an
edge for White - the weakened position of the white king here doesn't play any
role here.} *

