{If Black is delaying to fight for the centre with the d-pawn and does it with
the f-pawn instead, what will you do?} 10. exf6 {a standard reaction is to
exchange the pawns on f6 and let your opponent have to fix his central pawns
first. Black dreams to place them on d5 and e5 in order to obtain a strong
pawn centre but that is never going to happen.} Bxf6 {gxf6 weakens the king's
position too much, at least with the queens on the board.} 11. Nf5 $1 {
although a beautiful shot, this move might not be available in other similar
positions.} Nde7 12. Nxe7+ Bxe7 13. Be3 d5 14. c3 $1 $14 {[%csl Rc8,Gd4,Ge5]
[%cal Gf2f4,Gb1d2,Gd2f3] A key move for the structure - Black's central pawn
structure has been fixed, and they don't move forward anymore. Now you can get
to work on molesting the created weaknesses.} *

