Rxb7 with Na5. How should White play here?} 14. c4 $1 {[%cal Gg2b7] a typical
motif - with a pawn sacrifice White increases the power of the light-squared
bishop and the threat of Rxb7 becomes quite powerful.} (14. Rxb7 $6 Na5 15. Rb5
a6 16. Rb1 Nc4 {and Black is fine}) 14... d4 (14... dxc4 15. Rxb7 Na5 16. Qxd8
Bxd8 17. Rb1 Rc8 18. Ba3 $16 {[%cal Gh4f5,Gf5d6] and White wins material.}) 15.
Rxb7 Na5 16. Rb5 Rc8 17. Bh3 Rxc4 18. Nf5 $14 {[%cal Gc1g5] White's pieces are
far more active and greatly compensate the missing pawn.} *

